	<text>
		<body>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Saint Paul</placeName> <date>May the 6&#8212;<add>Hebrew</add>&#44; 5623</date></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">Revd Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)">I send you here an article&#44; I<lb/> consider it worthy to have a place in your valuable Occident&#44; But<lb/> after all I leave it to your own <sic>judgement</sic>&#44; do with it what you think<lb/> best&#44; as I have no patience to write with carefulness&#44; and you are all<lb/> ready acquainted with my bad writing&#44; you will understand well<lb/> my meaning&#44; and you will be so kind to arrange it&#44; and correct it as<lb/> it ought to be&#44; <add>Hebrew</add>&#44; besides I hope it will answer to the<lb/> Christians as well for their accusation&#44; with which they accuse us<lb/> being superstitious in not pronouncing the holy name.  Should the doctor<lb/> say any thing against it&#44; with the help of the Almighty we will be<lb/> able to answer him and to bruise his head.  Any how&#44; I would like to<lb/> know your opinion about what I have written&#44; till then&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(9)">I remain&#44; Dear and Revd Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(7)">your wisher&#44; one who loves you as himself</p>
			<p rend="indent(9)"><persName role="author">E. Marcuson</persName>.</p>
				<p>If you will be please to write to me&#44; write in care of <persName>Mr. Cardza.</persName></p>
		</body>
